JOHANNESBURG - Maps Maponyane is working hard to inspire the future generation with his The Bursary Network programme. The model, actor and public figure is using his The Bursary Network programme to take 19 students to school in the New Year. The Bursary Network helps crowdfunds tuition fees for deserving students who are struggling with funds to pursue their dreams. According to Maps Maponyane the network has managed to raise approximately R735 000 with the help of about 758 donors. The initiative is gaining momentum with some on showing interest and wanting to be part of the initiative. Not only did Twitter users congratulate and celebrate the notion of a brighter future for the students, one of the beneficiaries' sister also took the time to show Maponyane some gratitude. eNCA